message.entry: Sample offset must have a non-negative integer value.
Sample offset values outside the [0, SamplesPerSymbol*SymbolsPerTrace-1] range are wrapped to this range.
Samples per symbol must be a positive scalar integer.
Symbols per trace must be a positive scalar integer.
Traces to display must be a positive scalar integer.
Y-limits (Minimum) must be a real scalar.
Y-limits (Maximum) must be a real scalar.
Y-limits (Minimum) must be less than Y-limits (Maximum).
The number of symbols to plot exceeds the scope buffer size. Reduce the number Traces to display.

To ensure visual integrity, Eye Diagram blocks in conditionally executed subsystems need:\n1) An input length that is an integer multiple of 'Symbols per trace * Samples per symbol'\n2) Sample offset equal to 0.
All sample times for this block must be discrete.\nContinuous sample time is not allowed.

Set the oversampling method to ''None'' for highly oversampled
input signals (e.g., Samples per symbol x Symbols per trace > 64).
Otherwise, set it to ''Input interpolation'' or ''Histogram interpolation''
for low-noise and high-noise scenarios, respectively.

Set the color scale to ''Logarithmic'' when the eye diagram spread
is very narrow, either vertically or horizontally.
Histogram interpolation is not supported when the color scale is logarithmic. The color scale has been set to linear.
